# ü©∫ Smart Gut Monitor (SGM)

> **An AI-powered IoT system for non-invasive bowel sound monitoring and automated diagnosis.**

![Project Banner](https://via.placeholder.com/1000x300?text=Smart+Gut+Monitor+System) 
*(Tip: Replace this link with a screenshot of your React Dashboard later)*

## üìñ Overview
**Smart Gut Monitor** is a complete end-to-end system designed to assist gastroenterologists in diagnosing bowel diseases (like IBS) using Artificial Intelligence. The system captures bowel sounds via a piezoelectric sensor, processes them using a deep learning model (**CRNN**), and provides real-time analysis through a web dashboard.

## üöÄ Features
- **Real-time Monitoring:** Live streaming of bowel sounds from ESP32 to the dashboard.
- **AI Diagnosis:** Uses a **CRNN (Convolutional Recurrent Neural Network)** model to classify sounds as *Normal* or *Abnormal* with **99% Recall**.
- **IoT Integration:** Seamless serial communication between hardware and software.
- **Medical History:** Automatically saves analysis sessions to a **SQL Server** database for patient tracking.
- **Interactive Dashboard:** User-friendly **React** interface for doctors.

## üèóÔ∏è System Architecture
The system consists of four main layers:
1.  **Hardware Layer:** Piezo Sensor & ESP32 (Signal Acquisition).
2.  **Backend Layer:** FastAPI & Python (Data Processing & AI Inference).
3.  **Database Layer:** MS SQL Server (Data Persistence).
4.  **Frontend Layer:** React.js (Visualization & Control).

## üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack

| Component | Technology Used |
|-----------|----------------|
| **Hardware** | ESP32, Piezoelectric Sensor, C++ (Arduino IDE) |
| **AI Model** | PyTorch, CRNN (CNN + LSTM), Librosa (MFCC) |
| **Backend** | Python, FastAPI, Uvicorn, PySerial, PyODBC |
| **Frontend** | React.js, Axios, HTML/CSS |
| **Database** | Microsoft SQL Server |

## ‚öôÔ∏è Installation & Setup

### 1. Prerequisites
- Python 3.8+
- Node.js & npm
- SQL Server (Express or Developer edition)
- VS Code or PyCharm

### 2. Backend Setup
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone [https://github.com/maimamoon/SmartGut-Monitor-System.git](https://github.com/maimamoon/SmartGut-Monitor-System.git)
cd SmartGut-Monitor-System/backend

# Install Python dependencies
pip install fastapi uvicorn torch torchvision torchaudio pyserial librosa pyodbc numpy

# Run the API Server
uvicorn main:app --reload